<div class="article-text">
<p>Syndicated columnist Charles Krauthammer told viewers Monday on “Special Report with Bret Baier” that Republican presidential candidate Ted Cruz “highlighted the issue” by firing communications director Rick Tyler over a controversial video that falsely depicted Marco Rubio dismissing the Bible.</p><div class="mod-16 active"> <div class="ad-container flex"> <div class="ad gpt flex" data-ad-init="1" data-ad-slot-rendered="1" data-rendered-size="320x50" id="mobile-320x50_300x250"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/4145/fnc/politics_0__container__" style="border: 0pt none;"><iframe frameborder="0" height="50" id="google_ads_iframe_/4145/fnc/politics_0" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" name="google_ads_iframe_/4145/fnc/politics_0" scrolling="no" src="javascript:&quot;&lt;html&gt;&lt;body style='background:transparent'&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;&quot;" style="border: 0px none; vertical-align: bottom;" title="3rd party ad content" width="320"></iframe></div><iframe frameborder="0" height="0" id="google_ads_iframe_/4145/fnc/politics_0__hidden__" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" name="google_ads_iframe_/4145/fnc/politics_0__hidden__" scrolling="no" src="javascript:&quot;&lt;html&gt;&lt;body style='background:transparent'&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;&quot;" style="border: 0px none; vertical-align: bottom; visibility: hidden; display: none;" title="" width="0"></iframe></div> <p class="advert-txt">ADVERTISEMENT</p> </div> </div>
<p>The video shows Rubio walking into a hotel lobby past a staffer reading the Bible, and subtitles in the video misquote Rubio as telling the staffer, "Got a good book there, not many answers in it."</p>
<p>Krauthammer, a Fox News contributor, said that by firing his communications director, the Texas senator and a GOP presidential candidate gave Trump and Rubio “an opportunity to pile on with those rather rough tweets.” </p>
<p>He added that because of Cruz’s drastic reaction over Rubio video, the story became “the lead story” that everybody is talking about. </p>
<p>“I am not sure he [Cruz] has cured the problem at all,” he said.</p>
